title: Legacy credentialsPath match fails ~ vs absolute paths
updated_at: "2026-07-15T05:57:19Z"
---
## Problem
When legacy mode matches by `credentialsPath`, `pathsEqual` only compares raw/normalized strings and does not expand `~` or `$HOME`. Discovery emits absolute paths (`/home/…/.claude/.credentials.json`); config often stores `~/.claude/.credentials.json`. Match fails → discovered rows filtered out → fallback synthetic legacy row only if path set (works) or empty list if bootstrap path logic doesn’t align. Fragile and path-dependent.

## Location
contents/ui/ProfileController.qml:64-66

## Suggested fix
Expand `~`/`$HOME` to absolute before compare (or compare inodes via a small probe). Prefer matching by inode when discovery already ran.

